# ─── Rust / Cargo ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
target/
*.wasm.bak

# Compiled WASM artifacts (built, not stored in git)
*.wasm

# ─── Python ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.venv/
venv/
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/

# ─── Node / TypeScript SDK ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
node_modules/
dist/
build/
*.tsbuildinfo

# ─── OS / Editor ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ─── Secrets / Credentials ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx

# ─── Beads issue tracker ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# (detailed rules in .beads/.gitignore; these are the repo-root guards)
.beads-credential-key
.dolt/
# Dolt server is the source of truth (per memory + `bd context`). The JSONL
# snapshot is kept locally (.beads/snapshot.jsonl) for bootstrap of fresh
# clones via `bd import`, but never tracked — bd's upgrade-recovery path
# treats any file literally named `.beads/issues.jsonl` as "stale state to
# auto-reimport", causing a self-perpetuating dirty-dolt loop in v1.0.4.
# Renamed to snapshot.jsonl to dodge that magic name; ignore both for safety.
.beads/issues.jsonl
.beads/snapshot.jsonl

# ─── Debug / Observability ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Debug log written by the nervous-bus plugin adapter
.cache/
debug.jsonl
*.log

# ─── Misc build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.tmp
*.bak
*.orig

# ─── Autobench run outputs & caches ────────────────────────────────────────────
autobench/benchmarks/
autobench/data/
benchmarks/

# ─── Generated visualizations ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
pulse.png
sysmap.png

# ─── Log rotation artifacts (*.log already above; this catches rotated .log.1 etc.)
*.log.*

# ─── Per-run tool artifacts (keep .py/.md, ignore output data files) ───────────
tools/*.jsonl
tools/diversity_drift*.json
tools/ab_minimax*.json

# ─── Schema migration artifacts (naming convention *_v*.json, not authoritative)
schemas/*_v*.json

# Scratch from running deer-flow probes from this dir (host: ~/.cache/deer-flow/...)
.deer-flow/
# Claude Code scheduled task lock (per-machine)
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
# Claude Code per-machine settings — host hooks (bd prime) differ from
# loomie-container hooks (/usr/local/bin/hearth-loom-hook). Tracking this
# file caused loomies to commit container-internal hook paths back to the
# repo and break the host's Claude Code on every autoloom merge.
.claude/settings.json
# Claude Code session data — never commit any of .claude/ except settings.local.json
.claude/reports/
.claude/worktrees/
.claude/*.jsonl
.claude/*.lock

# Beads issue tracker internals — dolt DB, hooks, per-machine metadata
.beads/dolt/
.beads/hooks/
.beads/metadata.json
.beads/config.yaml
.beads/snapshot.jsonl
.beads/issues.jsonl

# Internal claims / EDD audits — not relevant to OSS contributors
claims/

# Internal research notes and benchmark run artifacts
tools/recovered_cycles/
tools/validation_cycles/
tools/*research*.md
tools/ab_minimax*.json
tools/multifile_refactor*.json
tools/variance_floor*.json
tools/check_minimax*.json
tools/burn-logs/

# HearthLoom-internal — do not commit
.hearth-loom/
.local_version
last-touched
.hearth-loom-failed-at
BLOCKED-*.md

# Loomie agent scaffold — per-worktree, not for the shared repo
.agent/
.antigravitycli/

# Private event contracts — these belong in $NERVOUS_HOME/schemas/ (the local
# overlay at ~/.config/nervous-bus/schemas/), NEVER in this public repo. See
# schemas/README.md for the full policy and prefix list.
#
# Adding a new private prefix here is MANDATORY when a schema describes
# anything not meant for public eyes. Update schemas/README.md too.
#
# tachyonos.* — private trading/prediction-market engine (tachyonac-engine):
#   PnL, positions, trades, venue/order data, proprietary strategy params.
schemas/tachyonos.*.json
docs/tachyonos-contract.md
#
# tengine.diag.* — internal diagnostics: work-tree telemetry, scheduling
#   internals, TSDL activation details. Not appropriate for public repo.
schemas/tengine.diag.*.json
#
# hearth.market.state.* — bridges tachyonos signals into hearth; raw_signal
#   field can carry private tachyonos payload.
schemas/hearth.market.state.*.json
